What does "open-door notes" refer to? Open-door notes are a type of communication between a doctor and a patient. They are handwritten notes that the doctor leaves for the patient to read. Open-door notes are a way for the doctor to communicate with the patient about their health and treatment.

In America-China relations, what does "open-door notes" refer to? The Open Door Notes were a series of diplomatic notes issued by the United States in the late 19th century. The notes called for equal trading rights for all countries in China and an end to the country's division into spheres of influence.
What fraction of the population of India used the internet in 2017? In 2017, only about one-third of the population of India used the internet.

What fraction of the population of India used the internet in the last three months? There is no definitive answer to this question as it depends on how you define "the population of India." However, according to the Internet Live Stats website, as of September 2017, about 39% of the population of India was using the internet.

Why does electrical current move through muscle faster than through fat? The speed of electrical current through muscle is faster than through fat because muscle is a better conductor of electricity than fat.
Why is muscle a better conductor of electricity than fat? Muscle is a better conductor of electricity than fat because it has more water and less fat.
